        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Trenton</placeName>
                <date>April 26. 1852</date>.</p>
            <p>My dear sir.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am very much obliged to you<lb/> for your kindness in sending me a
                copy<lb/> of your translation of <persName>Mendelssohn's</persName> Trea-<lb/>tise.
                Being about to leave town for<lb/> a few days I cannot wait until I<lb/> have recd
                it, to thank you, but I have<lb/> recd the autobiographical notices in<lb/> the
                "Introduction" its great interest.<lb/> If your industry shall not be <hi
                    rend="underline">rever</hi>-<lb/><hi rend="underline">de</hi> as it deserves
                    <del>it</del> to be, it cannot</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>fail, at least, to be <hi rend="underline">admired</hi>, &amp; to re-<lb/>ceive the
                esteem even of those who differ<lb/> most widely from you as to the object<lb/> to
                be attained.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is one of the mysteries of the<lb/> Divine Providence at which I
                would<lb/> most submissively bow my feeble un-<lb/>derstanding, that the human
                mind,<lb/> with equal sincerity of heart to know<lb/> the truth from the Scriptures,
                is so<lb/> diverse in its conclusions. But<lb/> I would be grateful at the same<lb/>
                time that the human heart is to</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>constitute that such sincere inqui-<lb/>rers, however diverse, may entertain<lb/> a
                cordial charity &amp; regard towards<lb/> one another. It is not for the first<lb/>
                time that I now include you in my<lb/> prayers for myself and all who love<lb/> the
                revealed truth &amp; wish to under-<lb/>stand &amp; follow it, that we may be<lb/>
                all guided by the same unerring<lb/> spirit that directed the sacred
                wri-<lb/>ters.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very truly &amp; respectfully yours</p>
            <p><persName role="author">John Hall</persName>.</p>
        </body>
